} is the volume of the unit cell. Note how this does not need to be an actual unit cell as seen in crystallography, it is indeed a representative volume of the material which in principle can be completely amorphous. As an amorphous material does not have a well defined crystal to define a volume, it can be calculated using the bulk density of the unit cell and the molecular weight: {\par
