\pard\plain\s3\ql\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\b\fs32\sl240\slmult1 \sb480 \fi0 1  Reflectivity from different interfaces\par
\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs20\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 To get to the reflectivity for multilayer instruments, we will start with the simplest case of reflectivity from a substrate. After that, we will expand this to the case of a single layer on top of a substrate, followed by a multilayer. \par
\pard\plain\s4\ql\sb240\sa120\keepn\f0\b\fs32\sl240\slmult1 \sb120 \fi0 1.1  Substrate\par
