\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs20\sl240\slmult1 \sb60 \fi0 Now if we add a single layer to the substrate, we will also have reflections from the finite thickness of this layer. The resulting reflection can most clearly be understood by tracing an incoming beam, as shown in figure {\field{\*\fldinst{\lang1024 REF BMsinglelayersketch \\* MERGEFORMAT }}{\fldrslt{@TitleReference {3.2}{An incoming neutron beam hits a single thin film from the substrate.}}}}. {\par
