}\pard\plain\s0\qj\widctlpar\f0\fs20\sl240\slmult1 \sb240 \fi0 As can be observed in figure, the difference in optical path between the reflected beams depends on the total thickness of one bilayer. The total thickness of one bilayer is known as the period, and is denoted with {{\u923*}} The position of the fringes that arise from the periodicities can be described in a similar way as equation {\field{\*\fldinst{\lang1024 REF BMreflectionsingle \\* MERGEFORMAT }}{\fldrslt{@TitleReference {3.4}{Single layer}}}}, but where we use the bilayer thickness instead of the individual layer thickness: {\par
