} and {{\field{\*\fldinst{ EQ {\i T}\\s\\do5({\fs16 {\i j}})}}{\fldrslt }}
} in this equation describe the reflected and transmitted amplitude for layer {{\i j}}. The fraction of these, {{\field{\*\fldinst{ EQ {\u967*}\\s\\do5({\fs16 {\i j}})}}{\fldrslt }}
} therefore describes the normalised intensity from each layer. The factor {{\field{\*\fldinst{ EQ {\i r}\\s\\do5({\fs16 {\i j}\\,{\i j}+1})}}{\fldrslt }}
} is the Fresnel coefficient for the interface, and can be written as: {\par
